There are diverse forms of love as there are of types of lovers. Love is found in all of human cultures and the type of love that exists in these different cultures portray different views as to what love is, placing the universal definition of what love really is, difficult to establish. See the [[Sapir-Whorf hypothesis]].
    −
===Interpersonal love===
+
===Interspecies love===
−
Interpersonal love is love between human beings, and is more sympathetic than the notion of very much ''liking'' for another. Although feelings are usually reciprocal, there can also be [[unrequited love]]. Interpersonal love is usually found in an [[interpersonal relationship]], such as between family members, friends, and couples. However, people often express love for other people outside of these relationships through compassionate outreach and volunteering.
+
Interspecies love is love between human beings and a variety of members of the animal kingdom, and is more sympathetic than the notion of very much ''liking'' for another. Although feelings are usually reciprocal, there can also be [[unrequited love]], such as when my dog decided to kill me with its personal shotgun. Interspecies love is usually found in an [[interspecies relationship]], such as between family members, friends, and couples, as well as satanic blood orgies. However, people often express love for other people outside of these relationships through compassionate outreach and volunteering.
